{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"sepia-cardiac-hawk","description":"# Adopt the DCO: Gerrit server-side enforcement, contributor docs, agent sign-off policy\n\n## Why\n\nrebar has no inbound-IP mechanism today (no DCO, no CLA). Both external reports and peer convergence recommend DCO over CLA: Qt's CLA is the stated reason it cannot accept PRs at all, and OpenStack replaced its CLA with the DCO effective July 2025 explicitly to lower the contribution barrier. OpenStack's implementation is the direct precedent for a Gerrit shop: enforce in Gerrit itself, not in CI — the server rejects an unsigned push at `refs/for/*` time, with zero new infrastructure and before any review or CI cycles are spent.\n\n## What\n\n- Set `receive.requireSignedOffBy = true` in `project.config` on `refs/meta/config` for the rebar Gerrit project (admin op — requires the JoeOakhartNava identity per this checkout's credential setup; see gerrit config-project-config docs).\n- CONTRIBUTING.md \"Sign your work (DCO)\" section using the moby/Docker template: link developercertificate.org, show the `Signed-off-by: Name <email>` trailer, `git commit -s`, the real-name requirement, a note that Gerrit rejects unsigned pushes at push time (a friendlier failure than a late red check), and an Envoy-style \"fixing DCO\" note (amend/rebase re-signing).\n- Agent/bot commits — adopt the Kubernetes-2026 norm (the responsible HUMAN signs off; AI is never a co-author): all RebarBotNava commits carry the sign-off of the responsible human using the registered bot email (exact form decided and documented here). Update CLAUDE.md / CLAUDE.local.md commit guidance and any commit-authoring automation so agent commits comply BEFORE enforcement flips — otherwise every agent push starts failing.\n- Migration order (strict): docs land → agent tooling/guidance updated and verified → server flag flipped → live verification. Existing history is NOT retrofitted (DCO applies to new commits only — kernel/OpenStack precedent).\n- Optionally flip GitHub's \"require sign-off on web-based commits\" setting on the mirror (harmless belt-and-braces; the mirror is read-only anyway).\n- Record the CLA decision: none unless Nava counsel requires inbound rights beyond Apache-2.0 §5 + DCO; note the escalation path (counsel review) without blocking on it.\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: Gerrit `project.config` change, CONTRIBUTING.md section, CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md commit-guidance updates, agent commit-convention update, live verification.\nOUT: CLA machinery; the probot/dco GitHub app (it watches PRs, which we bot-close — dead config); retrofitting or rewriting existing history; GitHub-side CI DCO checks (enforcement point is the Gerrit server).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] An unsigned push to `refs/for/main` is rejected by Gerrit with a clear message, and a signed push is accepted — both verified live, outcomes recorded on the ticket.\n- [ ] CONTRIBUTING.md DCO section present: developercertificate.org link, trailer format, `git commit -s`, real-name policy, fix-up instructions.\n- [ ] Agent-commit sign-off policy documented in CLAUDE.md guidance; agent-authored commits demonstrably carry the trailer before the server flag flips.\n- [ ] Migration order respected — no window in which agent/bot pushes fail (server flag flips last).\n- [ ] CLA decision + escalation path recorded on the ticket.","id":"ddcd-fc9e-a81f-4cbb","parent_id":"fc2a-9fa5-def6-4e68","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Adopt the DCO: Gerrit server-side enforcement, contributor docs, agent sign-off policy"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783628670123625001,"uuid":"cee952b5-71d1-4e87-8a2f-58ca9946c869"}